What changes could fix this warning? ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 3, 14, 54, 44, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'moki1202', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 663374584, 'comment_body': "Then we'd either need to add parameter descriptions here, or tell Roxygen to use the descriptions from somewhere else using one of [`@inheritParams`](https://roxygen2.r-lib.org/articles/rd.html#inheriting-documentation-from-other-topics), [`@describeIn`](https://roxygen2.r-lib.org/articles/rd.html#describein), or [`@rdname`](https://roxygen2.r-lib.org/articles/rd.html#rdname).", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 3, 15, 1, 31, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'infotroph', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 663474945, 'comment_body': "This doesn't work and I'd have known that if I'd run the package tests before submitting like I was supposed to! ðŸ™ˆ 

(apparently `dump.frames` binds both a local AND a global variable, so creating a local one produces weird masking effects! So since we only care here about the names and not the frame contents, instead I'm generating the names in the same way `dump.frames` does internally)

@robkooper please check this -- do you see any problems that I and testthat didn't think of?

```suggestion
    calls <- utils::limitedLabels(sys.calls())
```", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 4, 9, 27, 59, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'infotroph', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 663475924, 'comment_body': '(Recording the change in behavior produced by my `dump.frames`->`sys.calls` change below -- only accept this if accepting the other change too!)

```suggestion
## Fixed

* Logger calls no longer create a stray `dump.log` object in the global environment
```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 4, 9, 36, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'infotroph', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 663478764, 'comment_body': "@infotroph what's the sys.calls( ) here ?", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 4, 10, 0, 33, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'moki1202', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 663484214, 'comment_body': '@moki1202 You can see `help("sys.calls")` for full gory details, but basically it's a base R call that tells you the whole stack of functions currently being executed, i.e. it's how you find out whether you're calling `foo()` from inside `bar(baz(quux(foo())))` or just `quux(foo()))`. We're manipulating it here to print out a custom error that reports what function(s) produced the message. pr_body: this pull request is directed towards getting the `photosynthesis` package ready to be released to CRAN! I will be constantly updating this pull request as we move forward until the task is finished!
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 665218812, 'comment_body': "I haven't made any notable contributions to the photosynthesis package *yet*... but it's OK to leave this here and we'll see how much input I have into the rest of this PR :) ", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 7, 9, 49, 21, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'infotroph', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 665221836, 'comment_body': 'The importFrom is probably not needed -- calling functions directly from their namespace (`rjags::foo()`) is usually sufficient. We should test carefully after removing, though.

```suggestion
```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 7, 9, 53, 20, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'infotroph', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 665227142, 'comment_body': 'For cases like this where there's already a reasonably complete Roxygen block, I suggest keeping them as Roxygen comments and replacing `@export` with `@noRd` instead of converting the whole block to plain comments.

This is a reversal from what I suggested in PEcAn.logger, but here's my reasoning: It's a smaller and easier change, and it makes it explicit that the function is intentionally not exported or documented, whereas if converting to a plain comment someone might later see `# @param foo` and think "Oh, obviously that was supposed to be a Roxygen comment, let me fix that..."
```suggestion
##' @title shaded confidence interval
##' @name ciEnvelope
##' @author Mike Dietze
##' @noRd
```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 7, 10, 0, 21, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'infotroph', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 665248891, 'comment_body': "would '/document' still create a .Rd file for ciEnvelope? ", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 7, 10, 32, 29, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'moki1202', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 665275078, 'comment_body': 'Not with the `@noRd` tag present. If we were to remove the `@export` without adding `@noRd`, it would still create an Rd file -- which is sometimes desirable for cases where you want to document functions while keeping them internal, though not what we want in this case.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 7, 11, 15, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'infotroph', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 675867090, 'comment_body': "The parameter is misleadingly named, so I didn't catch this before: In this function `out` is the model output to be fitted, not an output directory.
```suggestion
##' @param out fitted model output from \code{\link{fitA}}
```", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 23, 21, 9, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'infotroph', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 675964403, 'comment_body': "@mdietze Should the JAGS requirement be updated to `>=`?  I'm currently testing with JAGS 4.3.0 and it all seems  to be working as advertised.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 24, 7, 44, 45, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'infotroph', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 676007589, 'comment_body': "Yeah, that's fine", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 24, 14, 46, 19, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'mdietze', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 676015210, 'comment_body': '```suggestion
SystemRequirements: JAGS (>=2.2.0)
```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 24, 15, 56, 51, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'infotroph', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: Fix remaining check warnings and undeclared dependencies from PEcAn.utils
